info.title: Rank Tracker API
info.description:
### Current version: 4

https://api.serpstat.com/v4 — Endpoint URL, through which all requests should be processed.

### API protocol

- Our API protocol is [**JSON-RPC 2.0**](https://www.jsonrpc.org/specification).

### Requests

- All requests should be sent via **POST** method.
- All request parameters must be set via POST request body in **JSON** format.
- Each request should contain a `method` name parameter corresponding to the API method (case-sensitive).

### Authentication

- Tokens are used for authentication. Create a token on [your profile page](https://serpstat.com/users/profile/). 
- `token` is required for all API requests.
- Api token is available for almost paid and trial plans that have API feature enabled.

### Pagination

For pagination, use the parameters:
- `size`: number of results per page (default 100, maximum 1000);
- `page`: page number (default is 1st page).

Please note: not all methods are supporting pagination.


### Filters

Filters can be applied to each method, most of them are specific for the method you used.
`filters` object are optional for most methods.

### Responses

- All responses are in **JSON** format.
- All responses have 200 HTTP status, even erroneous ones. In case of error, the response contains an `error` object instead of `result`.


### API credits (limits)

When calculating the used credits, your pricing plan's API requests are taken into account, including identical requests and requests for export.

### Request rates

Most subscription plans are limited to 1 request per second.
Top-tier plans allow up to 10 requests per second.
For higher rate limits, contact our sales team.
Exceeding your rate limit will result in an error response.

### Max results

The maximum number of results returned by each API method is limited up to 60,000 rows.

post.description:
The `RtApiSearchEngineProcedure.getProjectStatus` method returns the current status of the position update process (parsing) for the given project and region.
If the project is in parsing status, you should wait for its completion to get accurate results.

<!-- theme: success -->
> **Credits**: This method doesn't spent API credits.

parsing.description: Project parsing status:  `true` - project is currently parsing,  `false` - all ok, data is ready!

post.description:
The `RtApiSerpResultsProcedure.getUrlsSerpResultsHistory` method returns the ranking history of URLs for project keywords in the required region.
The data set is similar to the Rank tracker - SERP history.
 <!-- theme: success -->
> **Credits**: This method does not spend API credits.

pageSize.description:
Number of results per page.

Possible values: `20`, `50`, `100`, `200`, `500`

dateFrom.description: Start date of the period for which the data is required

dateTo.description: End date of the period for which the data is required

sort.description:
Sorting by parameters.

`date` — sorting by date,
`keyword` — sorting alphabetically

order.description:
Sorting order.

`desc` — descending order,
`asc` — ascending order

keywords.description:
Keywords for which pages and positions are required.

The maximum number of keywords that can be filtered is 1000.

withTags.description:
Display tags for the keywords.

`true` - show tags for the keywords,

`false` - don't show tags for the keywords.

domain.description:
Domain or page for which the data is required.

Data format:
`domain.com` — domain,
`https://domain.com/` — URL

data.description: Includes project-specific information and keyword details

domain.description: Domain or URL for which the search results are requested

frequency.description: Search volume per month in the selected country or city

expectedUrl.description: URL that is optimized for a specific keyword (if it was added in the project)

history.description: Historical ranking data for the keyword.

date.description: The date of the SERP data in `YYYY-MM-DD` format.

positions.description: A list of URLs and their rankings for the specified date

position.description: The rank position in the search results.

url.description: The URL ranking at the specified position

tags.description: A list of tags assigned to the keyword

id.description: The unique ID of the tag.

page.description: The current page number of the response.

page_total.description: The total number of pages available.

count.description: The number of results returned on the current page.

total.description: The total number of results available for the query.

spent_limits.description: The number of API credits consumed by this request. **This method does not spend API credits.**

post.description:
Use the `RtApiProjectProcedure.getProjects` method to get a list of your projects.
The method will save you time on getting information on your project ID, name, date of creation without the need of entering the platform.

<!-- theme: success -->
> **Credits**: This method does not spend API credits.

page.description: Page number in the projects list

pageSize.description: Number of results per page in the project list

createdAt.description: Date and time when the project was created

type.description: Project's type ("owner" — you are the owner of this project, "reader" — the project's owner is a member of your team. **In case you use Team management**.)

status.description:
Project status. 

`0` - deleted

`8` - active and not configured

`9` - active and configured.

enableTracking.description:
Availability of the Rank Tracker project by domain

`true` - Indicates either:
 - You have an active rank tracking for this project
 - Rank tracking hasn't been set up for this project yet

`false` - Indicates rank tracking has been disabled for this project

post.description:
The `RtApiSerpResultsProcedure.getTopCompetitorsDomainsHistory` method returns the list of domains for the required region, which were listed in the **top-20** for two any project keywords.

<!-- theme: success -->
> **Credits**: This method does not spend API credits.

dateFrom.description: Start date of the period for which the data is required

dateTo.description: Date of last withdrawal of positions

sort.description:
Sorting by parameters

Possible values:

`sum_traffic` — by traffic distribution,

`keywords_count` — by the number of keywords,

`avg_position` — by average position,

`position_ranges` — by position distribution tops,

`ads_count` — by number of ads

sortRange.description:
Possible values:

`top1\top2`... — position distribution by position,
`keywords_count_bottom\keywords_count_top` — distribution by ads,
`avg_position_top\avg_position_bottom` — average position by ads

order.description:
Possible values: 

`desc` — descending order,
`asc` — ascending order

domains.description: All domains in top 20 for two project keywords

domain.description: Domain that is appeared in top 20 by two project keyword

dates.description: Array with dates for the specified domain

date.description: Date for which the data of the domain is displayed

result.description:
`traffic_distribution`: Domain traffic distribution among all domains in top 20

`avg_position`: Domain average position, among the best positions for project keywords

`keywords_count`: Number of keywords which the domain is ranking for into search results

`keywords_by_ranges`: Keywords distribution by domain position range (top1 - top101)

`ads_count`: Number of ads for which domain is appeared in PPC

`keywords_count_blocks`: Keywords distribution by PPC blocks

`avg_position_blocks`: Average position distribution by PPC blocks

`top`: Top ad block

`sidebar`: Side ad block

`bottom`: Bottom ad block

traffic_distribution.description: Domain traffic distribution among all domains in top 20

avg_position.description: Domain average position, among the best positions for project keywords

keywords_count.description: Number of keywords which the domain is ranking for into search results

keywords_by_ranges.description: Keywords distribution by domain position range

top1.description: Keywords for which the domain took the 1 position

top3.description: Keywords for which the domain took the 2-3 positions

top5.description: Keywords for which the domain took the 4-5 positions

top10.description: Keywords for which the domain took the 6-10 positions

top20.description: Keywords for which the domain took the 11-20 positions

top101.description: Keywords for which the domain took the 21-100 positions in Google

page_total.description: Number of pages with the results for the selected parameter pageSize

spent_limits.description: This method does not spend API credits.
